gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 126, Cavaliers 116
gameRecap.excerpt: Milwaukee defeated Cleveland, 126-116, to snap their eight-game win streak while the Bucks won their third in a row. Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded his seventh triple-double of the season (42nd of career, fifth since Jan. 1), leading the way with 35 points, 18 rebounds, and 10 assists, as Damian Lillard (28 points, four assists) and Khris Middleton (24 points, five rebounds, five assists). Donovan Mitchell led the way with 23 points, seven rebounds, and eight assists while Jarrett Allen recorded his 13th straight double-double (21 points, 12 rebounds) for the Cavaliers in a losing effort. The Bucks improve to 31-13 as the Cavaliers fall to 26-16.
